# Network Transformer Selection Guide for IoT Ethernet

This guide covers transformer selection for IoT Ethernet designs,
where power budget, compact footprint, and wide temperature range
differ significantly from standard networking equipment.

## Why IoT Ethernet Needs Different Transformer Consideration

| Parameter | Standard Ethernet | IoT Device |
|-----------|------------------|------------|
| Power budget | Unconstrained | Milliwatt-level |
| Operating temp | 0°C to +70°C | −40°C to +85°C |
| PCB footprint | Flexible | Compact (often <50×50mm) |
| PHY power mode | Continuous | EEE/LPI sleep cycles |
| PoE usage | Optional | Common (cable-powered sensors) |
| MOQ needed | High volume | 50–500 pcs (prototype/NPI) |

