## Key Selection Criteria for IoT

### 1. Operating Temperature
Standard (commercial):  0°C to +70°C   — indoor office only

Industrial grade:       −40°C to +85°C — minimum for IoT deployment
OCL must be guaranteed across the full temperature range.

"350µH at 25°C" ≠ "350µH at −40°C" — request temperature curves.

### 2. Package Size
- Target: ≤ 8×8mm SMD footprint for 10/100BASE-TX
- Height: < 3mm for compact IoT designs
- Option: Magnetic jack (transformer + RJ45 combined) for maximum space saving

### 3. Energy Efficient Ethernet (EEE / 802.3az)
- PHY enters Low Power Idle (LPI) between packets
- Transformer must wake cleanly from LPI without elevated insertion loss
- Verify EEE compatibility with specific PHY before production commit

### 4. DCR for Power Budget
Power loss from DCR:  P = I² × DCR × (number of windings)

Lower DCR = less heat, better for power-constrained IoT designs

### 5. PoE-Powered IoT (802.3af/at)
- Standard signal transformer: NOT suitable (saturates under DC bias)
- PoE-rated transformer required for any PoE PSE or PD design
- 802.3af: 350mA DC bias | 802.3at: 600mA | 802.3bt: up to 960mA

## IoT Transformer Checklist
[ ] PHY datasheet / app note reviewed

[ ] OCL ≥ 350µH guaranteed at −40°C to +85°C

[ ] SMD package ≤ 8×8mm

[ ] Low DCR variant selected (if power budget critical)

[ ] EEE/LPI compatibility confirmed with PHY

[ ] PoE-rated if design uses PoE power

[ ] 1500V AC isolation (IEEE 802.3 minimum)

[ ] Supplier supports small MOQ (≥ 50pcs for IoT NPI)

